{"lemma":"غُدْوَةٌ","slug":"غُدْوَةٌ","root":"غ.د.#","root_slug":"غ-د-_","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-د-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31539"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%92%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"synonym of غَدَاة (ḡadāh)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"synonym of غَدَاة (ḡadāh); daybreak, dawn, early morning"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of غَدَا (ḡadā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lunch"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"morning errand"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31539","headword_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ","root":"gdw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, &c.,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadowapN","text_ar":"غَدْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", said by MF to be well known, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gidowapN","text_ar":"غِدْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", said by him to be rare, or disapproved, (TA,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"early part of the morning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first part of the day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period between the time of the prayer of daybreak and sunrise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaApN","text_ar":"غَدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadiy~apN","text_ar":"غَدِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) the last [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadoyapi","text_ar":"غَدْيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but correctly] a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHiy~apN","text_ar":"ضَحِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHowapN","text_ar":"ضَحْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaApN","text_ar":"غَدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHowapN","text_ar":"ضَحْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"early part of the forenoon, after sunrise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the sun is yet low;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to others,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the sun is somewhat high"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) [it may therefore be generally rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"morning, before,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after, sunrise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pls. are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudFY","text_ar":"غُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadawaAtN","text_ar":"غَدَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, TA,) which is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaApN","text_ar":"غَدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guduw~N","text_ar":"غُدُوٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) which is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", formed by rejecting the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of the sing.], or, accord. to the M, an anomalous pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaApN","text_ar":"غَدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, as J says, [in the S,] referring to the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@logaduw~i","text_ar":"بِا@لْغَدُوِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@loA=SaAli","text_ar":"وَا@لْا=صَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [vii. 204 and xiii. 16 and xxiv. 36],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlguduw~i","text_ar":"بِالغُدُوِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"there means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlgadawaAti","text_ar":"بِالغَدَوَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is a verb [i. e. an inf. n.] used to denote the time, as [is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluwE","text_ar":"طُلُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluwEa Al$~amosi","text_ar":"طُلُوعَ الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY waqoti TuluwEi Al$ms","text_ar":"فِى وَقْتِ طُلُوعِ الشمس"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadiy~aAtN","text_ar":"غَدِيَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K, TA, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadayAtN","text_ar":"غَدَياتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) which is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadiy~apN","text_ar":"غَدِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaAyaA","text_ar":"غَدَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) which is likewise a pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadiy~apN","text_ar":"غَدِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to IAar, and, if so, regularly formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaAyiwu","text_ar":"غَدَايِوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the same manner as has already been expl. in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$aAyaA","text_ar":"عَشَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iy~apN","text_ar":"عَشِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iY~N","text_ar":"عَشِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; by some said to be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this has been controverted by IHsh in the Expos. of the “ Kaabeeyeh ” and by its commentator ['AbdEl-Kádir] El-Baghdádee; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaAyaA","text_ar":"غَدَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not used except in conjunction with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$aAyaA","text_ar":"عَشَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~iY laA=tiyhi biAlgadaAyaA waAlEa$aAyaA","text_ar":"اـِنِّى لَا=تِيهِ بِالغَدَايَا وَالعَشَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I come to him in the early parts of mornings and in the late parts of evenings"},{"kind":"text","text":"], for the purpose of conformity. (S, TA.) Zj says that when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowap","text_ar":"غُدْوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bukorap","text_ar":"بُكْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"early part of the morning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the present day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a particular day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is imperfectly decl.: and AHei says that it is thus accord. to the opinion commonly obtaining, as is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bukorap","text_ar":"بُكْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", each as being a generic proper name, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usaAmapu","text_ar":"اُسَامَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that when you mean to generalize, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN waqotu na$aATK","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ وَقْتُ نَشَاطٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An early part of a morning is a time of briskness, liveliness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightliness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and when you mean to particularize,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^asiyran~a All~ayolapa A_ilaY gudowapa","text_ar":"لَاَسِيرَنَّ اللَّيْلَةَ اـِلَى غُدْوَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly journey to-night until the early part of the morning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [in the latter case also] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuhu gudowapa","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُهُ غُدْوَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him in the early part of the morning of this,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a particular, day"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gdwp","text_ar":"غدوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here imperfectly decl. because it is determinate, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHara","text_ar":"سَحَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but it is of those adv. ns. that may be used otherwise than as adv. ns.: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyra EalaY farasika gudowapa","text_ar":"سِيرَ عَلَى فَرَسِكَ غُدْوَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapF","text_ar":"غُدْوَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Journeying was performed on thy horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mare, in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowap","text_ar":"غُدْوَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of this,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a particular, day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowap","text_ar":"غُدْوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the journey of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowap","text_ar":"غُدْوَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of this,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a particular, day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the journey of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowap","text_ar":"غُدْوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was performed"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was journeyed"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on thy horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mare,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapu","text_ar":"غُدْوَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyrapu","text_ar":"مَسِيرَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapa","text_ar":"غُدْوَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyrapu gudowapK","text_ar":"مَسِيرَةُ غُدْوَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahorN","text_ar":"شَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur xxxiv. 11 is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyrapu $ahorK","text_ar":"مَسِيرَةُ شَهْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; what is with tenween, of these, being indeterminate, and what is without tenween being determinate. (S. [In one of my copies of the S,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siro","text_ar":"سِرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyra","text_ar":"سِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": that the latter is the right is shown by the addition of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapu","text_ar":"غُدْوَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for each of these must be what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAy^ibN Eano faAEilK","text_ar":"نَايِبٌ عَنْ فَاعِلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. a substitute for an agent.]) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaApN","text_ar":"غَدَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["TA","K","IAar","Msb","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}